"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The use of the apply function with a lambda function in this context is incorrect because it returns a Series for each group, which cannot be directly assigned to a new column in the original DataFrame. This will lead to a ValueError due to mismatched indices when trying to assign the result back to df['z']. Instead, the operation should be performed in a way that ensures the result aligns with the original DataFrame's index.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).transform(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\\n\"}"